# Retest

🔁 Simple Definition

After a breakout:

Price breaks a level

Then returns to that same level

Then decides: hold or fail


👉 That return = retest


---

📈 In an Upward Breakout

Before:

Resistance = 100


After breakout:

Price goes above 100

Then comes back to ~100


Two possibilities:

✅ Good retest (real breakout)

Price touches 100

Holds above it

Moves up again


👉 Resistance becomes support


---

❌ Failed retest (fake breakout)

Price comes back to 100

Breaks below it again

Drops


👉 Breakout was false


---

📉 In a Downward Breakout

Same idea but reversed:

Support breaks → becomes resistance

Price comes back → rejects → goes lower



---

🧠 Why retest happens

Traders who missed the breakout enter

Big players confirm the level

Market checks if the breakout is accepted



---

🔍 Visual idea

Before: After breakout: Retest:
------ ----------- --------
 100 105 105
 100 → break → 105 → pullback → 100 ← retest
 100 105 110 ↑


---

⚡ Why traders LOVE retests

Because it gives:

Safer entry

Clear stop-loss

Confirmation


👉 Instead of chasing, you let price prove itself.


---

🚨 Golden rule

Don’t buy the breakout → buy the retest

This alone can massively reduce fake breakout losses.
